13:23.309 --> 13:25.877
Doesn't matter.

13:25.878 --> 13:28.580
The point is,
if you tell, I'll tell.

13:28.581 --> 13:29.848
Go ahead.

13:29.849 --> 13:31.083
Tell him.

13:31.084 --> 13:33.018
If my husband leaves me,
I'll still have Charlie.

13:33.019 --> 13:35.220
But if I tell everyone
what you've been up to,

13:35.221 --> 13:36.455
what will you have?

13:38.291 --> 13:40.192
Crap.

13:40.193 --> 13:43.161
Oopsie-doopsie,
watch your poopsie.

13:48.735 --> 13:52.237
There's a bird
on your husband's head.

13:52.238 --> 13:54.106
Yeah. So?

14:00.580 --> 14:02.013
Crap.

14:02.014 --> 14:04.249
♪ Men. ♪

14:06.655 --> 14:08.389
♪ Men. ♪

14:09.958 --> 14:11.058
This is your husband?

14:11.059 --> 14:12.860
This is Manny Quinn?

14:12.861 --> 14:15.529
Oh, my God, Manny Quinn.

14:15.530 --> 14:17.097
Your husband's a dummy.

14:17.098 --> 14:21.201
To be fair, he wasn't the one
fooled by a mannequin.

14:21.202 --> 14:24.672
What do you use to get
bird poop off a husband?

14:24.673 --> 14:26.340
Charlie thinks
you're actually married.

14:26.341 --> 14:29.276
Uh, yeah,
that's kind of the idea.

14:29.277 --> 14:31.211
I'm not gonna let you
scam him like that.

14:31.212 --> 14:33.147
I understand.

14:33.148 --> 14:35.015
What's that, Manny?

14:35.016 --> 14:36.684
I hadn't even thought of that.

14:36.685 --> 14:37.618
Thought of what?

14:37.619 --> 14:39.186
What did he--
What are you saying?

14:39.187 --> 14:40.754
How much would you need
to pay back

14:40.755 --> 14:42.389
all the money you stole
from your family?

14:42.390 --> 14:44.058
I didn't steal, they invested.

14:44.059 --> 14:45.059
Fine. How much?

14:45.060 --> 14:46.493
$50,000.

14:46.494 --> 14:48.862
Why don't you wait here
and I'll go get my checkbook.

14:48.863 --> 14:50.264
Oh, no, no, no, no, no, no, no.

14:50.265 --> 14:51.699
I-I am loyal to my brother.

14:51.700 --> 14:53.500
You can't buy my silence
with a check.

14:53.501 --> 14:56.370
- You want cash?
- You have cash?

14:56.371 --> 14:58.489
I mean, I won't betray Charlie!

15:01.576 --> 15:03.777
You may have to kill him.

15:05.547 --> 15:07.781
♪ Men. ♪

15:09.968 --> 15:11.985
Well, hey, uh, what are you
still doing here?

15:11.986 --> 15:13.487
I need my money back.

15:13.488 --> 15:14.755
Why?

15:14.756 --> 15:15.889
Just found out

15:15.890 --> 15:17.458
two of my teenage granddaughters
are pregnant.

15:17.459 --> 15:19.326
At the same time?

15:19.327 --> 15:20.728
By the same guy.

15:20.729 --> 15:23.430
Long story short,
I need cash quick.

15:23.431 --> 15:24.765
Uh, o-okay.

15:24.766 --> 15:26.200
Um, how much are we talking?

15:26.201 --> 15:28.936
All of it.
A-All of it?

15:28.937 --> 15:30.070
Is that a problem?

15:30.071 --> 15:33.607
No, no, it's not a-a problem.

15:33.608 --> 15:37.644
Um... if you want cash,
um, you'll have to wait

15:37.645 --> 15:40.280
till tomorrow,
so I can go to the bank.

15:40.281 --> 15:41.115
Tomorrow's fine.

15:41.116 --> 15:42.383
Good, good.

15:42.384 --> 15:44.451
Of course you're gonna
lose quite a bit

15:44.452 --> 15:45.519
by pulling out early.

15:45.520 --> 15:48.555
Yeah, well, if Jimmy
Lee had done the same,

15:48.556 --> 15:51.158
I wouldn't
need the money.

15:53.011 --> 15:55.429
Okay, tomorrow!

15:55.430 --> 15:57.331
Oh, boy.

15:57.332 --> 15:59.533
BAD ALAN:
Don't panic.

15:59.534 --> 16:01.685
In the toaster, numb-nuts.

16:03.521 --> 16:04.972
Okay, Mr. Smart Guy.

16:04.973 --> 16:06.874
How do you suggest
I pay off Berta?

16:06.875 --> 16:08.175
I spent all the money.

16:08.176 --> 16:09.076
On what?

16:09.077 --> 16:10.177
Well, you know,

16:10.178 --> 16:13.580
clothing, jewelry, electronics,
a little lipo.

16:13.581 --> 16:15.048
Liposuction?

16:15.049 --> 16:17.050
I had a bit of a muffin top.

16:17.051 --> 16:20.421
You know, I actually feel
a lot better about myself now.

16:20.422 --> 16:22.122
Okay, well, um,

16:22.123 --> 16:23.924
then you're gonna
have to get another investor.

16:23.925 --> 16:25.092
What about the goofy chick?

16:25.093 --> 16:26.393
Rose?

16:26.394 --> 16:28.328
She did offer me $50,000.

16:28.329 --> 16:29.696
Why didn't you take it, schmuck?

16:29.697 --> 16:32.733
Because if I took it, I would
have to betray my brother.

16:32.734 --> 16:34.001
Hey, Alan.

16:34.002 --> 16:35.269
Who you talking to?

16:35.270 --> 16:36.270
Nobody.

16:36.271 --> 16:37.938
Want some toast?

16:37.939 --> 16:39.406
Maybe later. Check it out.

16:39.407 --> 16:40.874
Two first-class tickets
to Paris.

16:40.875 --> 16:41.842
We're going to Paris?

16:41.843 --> 16:42.926
Great idea.

16:42.927 --> 16:44.912
Can we leave before
the banks open tomorrow?

16:44.913 --> 16:46.180
What?!

16:46.181 --> 16:47.547
Are you out of your mind?

16:47.548 --> 16:48.715
I'm taking Rose.

16:48.716 --> 16:50.317
Did you know they have
their own Disneyland there,

16:50.318 --> 16:51.552
and they serve wine?

16:51.553 --> 16:54.521
But what about her husband?

16:54.522 --> 16:56.690
I'm gonna ask her
to leave him and marry me.

16:56.691 --> 17:00.461
Oh, gee, Charlie,
that may not be the best idea.

17:00.462 --> 17:02.362
I don't recall
asking for your opinion.

17:02.363 --> 17:04.832
Hey, hey,
I'm just looking out for you.

17:04.833 --> 17:07.000
Do me a favor,
a little less looking out,

17:07.001 --> 17:08.969
little more moving out.

17:10.505 --> 17:11.972
You're right.
Screw him.

17:11.973 --> 17:13.507
Okay, let's go get that cash

17:13.508 --> 17:15.576
from the crazy chick
who married the mannequin.

17:15.577 --> 17:16.742
She's crazy?

17:16.743 --> 17:18.512
I'm the one talking to
a kitchen appliance.

17:18.512 --> 17:22.266
Hey, look,
I'm trapped in a toaster.

17:24.853 --> 17:27.320
Wait, wait, I'm coming with you!

17:29.557 --> 17:31.775
♪ Men. ♪

17:32.593 --> 17:34.311
I think that's
everything.

17:34.312 --> 17:36.313
So what did you
tell your husband?

17:36.314 --> 17:37.648
I didn't have to
tell him anything.

17:37.649 --> 17:39.316
He's in New York
for a big fashion show.

17:39.317 --> 17:40.367
Perfect.

17:40.368 --> 17:42.436
So what kind of clothes
he design anyway?

17:42.437 --> 17:44.371
Men's sportswear, mostly.

17:44.372 --> 17:45.405
Anything I might like?

17:45.406 --> 17:46.840
No, it's more the kind of stuff

17:46.841 --> 17:47.841
Alan would wear.

17:47.842 --> 17:50.110
Oh, so, tacky.

17:50.111 --> 17:53.947
You know, I think I left
my raincoat in the bedroom.

17:53.948 --> 17:55.132
I'll get it.

17:55.133 --> 17:58.218
Oh, thanks.

17:58.219 --> 18:00.787
Uh-oh.

18:06.828 --> 18:08.428
Whoa.

18:09.998 --> 18:14.134
I guess the guy brings
his work home with him.

18:16.004 --> 18:17.271
Yep.

18:17.272 --> 18:19.506
Tacky.

18:21.359 --> 18:23.377
I got it!

18:25.146 --> 18:26.880
♪ Men. ♪

18:29.326 --> 18:31.127
♪ Men. ♪

18:31.128 --> 18:33.529
Here is your $10,000.

18:33.530 --> 18:35.431
Hope it works out with
your granddaughters.

18:35.432 --> 18:37.366
They're 15 years old
and pregnant.

18:37.367 --> 18:40.703
What should I look forward to,
the next season of <i>Teen Mom?</i>

18:42.573 --> 18:43.973
And that is it.

18:43.974 --> 18:46.509
Everybody is paid off.

18:46.510 --> 18:47.977
But you're broke again.

18:47.978 --> 18:49.912
But my conscience is clear.

18:49.913 --> 18:52.315
Dy-no-mite!

18:53.450 --> 18:56.752
The rhyming thing
really wasn't working.

18:56.753 --> 18:58.487
Leave me alone.

18:58.488 --> 19:00.089
All you are is my dark side.

19:00.090 --> 19:02.658
Fine, would you rather
listen to your light side?

19:02.659 --> 19:03.826
What are you talking about?

19:03.827 --> 19:05.795
There's more of us
in here, buddy.

19:05.796 --> 19:07.797
More?

19:07.798 --> 19:09.665
Oh, really?

19:09.666 --> 19:11.167
That shirt with those pants?

19:11.168 --> 19:12.835
What were you thinking?

19:15.706 --> 19:17.673
Okay, who else you got?

19:17.674 --> 19:19.041
Who else do you need?

